        <abstract>
            <p>Answers a number of queries from Lyell concerning geography and geology of Chiloé Island and its relationship to the Cordilleras.</p>
            <p>Asks about "perched rocks" on Jura and notes their relevance to Louis Agassiz’s theory. Discusses Agassiz’s view on Jura.</p>
            <p>Mentions seeing Robert Brown.</p>
            <p>Notes R. I. Murchison’s discovery of shells in central England.</p>
            <p>Weakness of negative evidence.</p>
        </abstract>
